esource-manager.tsx:355:                <span className=\"field-label-row\">Enabled in resource catalogs <HelpTooltip text=\"Enabled resources appear in future MCP resources/list runtime handlers. Disabled resources stay editable but should not be readable by clients.\" /></span>\ndocs/PRODUCT_SENSE.md:45:- MCP client-side sampling, roots, elicitation, or task-augmented execution in MVP\ndocs/product-specs/oauth-consent-and-token-runtime.md:12:- OAuth user, client, token filter, and permission inputs expose concise hover tooltips explaining login credentials, token TTLs, client credentials, redirect URIs, allowed tools/resources/prompts, grants, subjects, and client filters\ndocs/product-specs/oauth-consent-and-token-runtime.md:24:- approving consent creates a single-use-ready authorization code bound to client, redirect URI, user, selected tools/resources/prompts, resource/audience, optional PKCE challenge, state, expiry, and unused status, then redirects with `code` and `state`\ndocs/product-specs/oauth-consent-and-token-runtime.md:30:- client-credentials tokens use the client credentials TTL, subject `client:<client_id>`, `grant_type=client_credentials`, and permissions equal to all client-allowed tools/resources/prompts when no scope is requested or the intersection of requested `endpoint:<endpoint_id>`, `resource:<resource_id>`, and `prompt:<prompt_id>` scopes and client-allowed sets when scope is present\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
